Getting Started
Clone the Repository:

Prerequisites

I highly recommend having DBeaver https://dbeaver.io for this project.

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ghost-archive-database.git
cd ghost-archive-database
Database Setup:

Create a new database in your preferred SQL environment.
Execute the ghost_archive_schema.sql script to set up the tables and relationships.
Configurations:

Modify the script or tables if needed, based on your specific requirements.
Tables Overview
People:

Information about individuals, including personal details and relationships.
Families:

Representation of nuclear families with family history.
Articles:

Details about articles, including titles, summaries, content, and authors.
ArticleNames:

Associations between articles and names (people, places, organizations).
Orgs:

Information about organizations, including names, bios, and addresses.
Locs:

Details about locations, including names, information, and addresses.
Addresses:

Storage for addresses, linked to individuals, organizations, and locations.
PeopleNames:

Store various names associated with individuals.
FamilyMembers:

Establishment of family relationships.
Casefile:

Storage for information related to investigative cases.
Populating the Database
Execute SQL queries to insert data into the respective tables.
Modify the provided example data according to your specific use case.
Queries and Use Cases
Use SQL queries to extract meaningful information from the database.
Example queries for common use cases can be found in the example_queries.sql file.
Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you have improvements, additional features, or bug fixes, feel free to fork the repository and submit a pull request.

